<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
his Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin held cordial and friendly
talks here today.
</P>
<P>
Both pledged to further strengthen the two countries' strategic
partnership of equality and mutual confidence oriented toward the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Yeltsin's contribution to the
establishment of the strategic partnership, saying it fully
conforms with the fundamental interests of the two peoples and is
in line with the trend of the world situation.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that they shared identical views on current
international situation and the same positions on a number of
major international issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
