<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordanian, Iraqi Ministers Meet on Petroleum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Jordan and Iraq today discussed how
to strengthen bilateral cooperation in the fields of petroleum and
energy, particularly transport of Iraqi crude oil into Jordan
through pipelines.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here, the Jordanian Minister of Energy and Mineral
Resources Mohammed Saleh Hourani and his Iraqi counterpart Amir
Mohammed Rashid also discussed petroleum and gas prospect and
exploitation in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, the Jordanian minister described the
meeting as fruitful. He pointed out that the supply of Iraqi crude
oil and by-products to Jordan is proceeding in a satisfactory
manner as planned.
</P>
<P>
Under the oil-for-food accord between Iraq and the U.N., Iraq
is permitted to sell 2 billion dollars worth of oil to buy back
food and other necessities for its 19 million citizens suffering
from the U.N.-sanctions after the Gulf war.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, which sided with Iraq during the Gulf crisis, has been
striving to hold a bigger share in the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
