<HEADLINE> Bank, Petrochemical Firm Set Up Cooperative Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) Shanghai Branch and the Shanghai
Petrochemical Stocking Company Ltd. signed an agreement here today
to form a cooperative relationship.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, the bank will provide the firm with 700 million
yuan in loans this year to be used for a renovation project.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ICBC branch has also agreed to assist the firm's
restructuring of its financial management by using the bank's
advantages in capital management, clearance networking and
computer application.
</P>
<P>
The petrochemical company is one of the largest of its kind in
China, with pretax profits surpassing two billion yuan in 1996. It
has been listed in Hong Kong and US stock markets.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the bank has loaned 4.5 billion yuan to the
petrochemical firm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
