<HEADLINE> World's Leading Insurance Firm Opens Office in Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- AXA-UAP, one of the largest
insurance company's in the world, today opened its office in
Wuhan, capital of Central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The French insurance firm now protects assets worth some 450
billion US dollars, ranking first in this regard globally, while
its income ranks second.
</P>
<P>
AXA-UAP's network, which covers 50 countries, entered the
Chinese market in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The company also has offices in Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou
and plans to open another one in west China.
</P>
<P>
Only a few Chinese cities such as Shanghai have allowed foreign
insurance firms to do insurance business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
