<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-23 16:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Parliament Condemns German Ruling of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament today issued a
statement condemning a German court's rule on the Mykonos case as
"a flagrant violation of human rights."
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the statement
was endorsed by 160 members of the Iranian Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Berlin court verdict on April 10 on the Mykonos case, which
implicated top Iranian leaders' order to kill four Kurdish
opposition leaders in a Berlin restaurant five years ago, sparked
a crisis in relations between Iran and Germany and other European
countries.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the MPs strongly criticized the German
Parliament's action to support "the political and illegal verdict"
of the Berlin court and called it a hasty decision.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that "German support to the terrorist groups
is a flagrant violation of human rights."
</P>
<P>
It also called on the government to review Iran's future ties
with Germany.
</P>
<P>
Germany and Iran had recalled their ambassadors and expelled
four diplomats from each side. Ambassadors from European Union
member nations, except Greece, were also recalled from Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the diplomatic battle between Bonn and Tehran has
calmed down and the two sides have expressed their hope that
neither of them would like to sever the bilateral relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
