<HEADLINE> US Wage Gap Narrowing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Earnings inequality in the
United States is not getting worse, according to a new study by
the Urban Institute.
</P>
<P>
The results of its survey go against people's common belief
that the wage gap is widening in the country. But unlike most
other studies, the institute looked at differences in hourly pay,
not total pay.
</P>
<P>
It found that earnings inequality fell by 5.5 percent from 1987
to 1994.
</P>
<P>
A separate measure of wage inequality between the very highly
paid and the very poorly paid also declined -- by 7.1 percent --
in the same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
