<HEADLINE> UEFA May Discuss Change of Champions League Format </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- European soccer's governing body
UEFA may discuss a proposal made by Juventus to change the format
of champions league in the future.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, the reigning European Cup champion and finalist again
this year, has proposed that future Champions Cup semifinals and
finals be played within one week in the same country.
</P>
<P>
This year's seven other quarterfinal teams have backed the
idea, which would help reduce the congestion of domestic and
European matches.
</P>
<P>
UEFA has indicated it will consider doing away with the
two-legged semifinals and having a four-team showdown in one
venue. It could allow UEFA to switch from six groups of four
teams to four groups of six clubs.
</P>
<P>
"All the other quarterfinalists reacted very positively to
(Juventus managing director Roberto) Bettega's plan," UEFA
spokesman Fritz Ahlstrom said. "And so did UEFA. That means we
will discuss it but it would not be possible before the 1998-99
season." 
</P>
