<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commentary: Five-Nation Accord A Fresh Model for Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A brand-new model for safeguarding
regional security has emerged in an agreement signed here today on
reduction of military forces along border areas between China and
neighboring Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The first of its kind in the Asia-Pacific region, the accord
not only serves the interest of the five signatories but also
represents a fresh move toward handling inter-state issues through
peaceful and trustful means.
</P>
<P>
Talks on the accord, significant both politically and
militarily, lasted more than seven years. During the period, all
parties showed their confidence in each other. Mutual
understanding and cooperation helped find an eventual solution to
the complicated and sensitive issue.
</P>
<P>
Such a process and outcome fully manifest a wise sense of
security differing from the Cold War mentality. As China has kept
promoting in recent years the establishment of a new world order,
peaceful ways, instead of use of force, should always be sought to
settle inter-state disputes and conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The process of world multipolarization has been accelerating
since the end of the Cold War. The dominant theme of the current
world is striving for an international environment of peace and
stability conducive to development and prosperity for all.
</P>
<P>
However, the world is far from being peaceful. Hegemonism and
power politics are still pursued by some forces. It is not rare to
see them handling relations with others, either bilateral or
multilateral, in an unfair way, causing instability and tension
among nations.
</P>
<P>
China has always maintained that the establishment of a fair
and rational new world order should be based on the principles of
equality and mutual benefit, mutual respect for each others'
sovereignty and territorial integrity, non-aggression,
non-interference in each others' internal affairs and peaceful
co-existence. These principles have become a consensus of the
majority in the world.
</P>
<P>
This unprecedented accord reflects the five nations'
determination to strengthen cooperation and ensure a peaceful
development in the region.
</P>
<P>
By undertaking the obligations provided in the accord, the five
nations have presented to the world a bright prospect of the
region featuring peace and stability in the run to the 21st
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
