<HEADLINE> Various Departments Join in Fight Against Drug-Related Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Various departments and judicial
bodies have joined the Ministry of Public Security to carry out
China's targeted fight against drugs which was launched early this
month.
</P>
<P>
The National Committee of Narcotics Control (NCNC) announced
today its member departments of customs, chemical industry, public
health and others have spelled out specific measures for
intensifying the anti-drug campaign among the offices nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The General Administration of Customs (GAC) ordered all customs
agencies to focus on investigating criminal gangs involved in drug
smuggling, and improve their management over imported chemicals
that could be processed into drugs, especially natural Chinese
ephedra which is used to make "ice."
</P>
<P>
"The anti-drug campaign should move ahead shoulder to shoulder
with our anti-smuggling drive," the GAC said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Chemical Industry has launched a public
education campaign among its employees to raise their awareness of
the harmful effects of many of the materials they handle.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry will also conduct a comprehensive survey on the
situations of the production, dealing, transportation, use,
importing and exporting of chemicals that could be made into drugs.
</P>
