<HEADLINE> EU Urges Member States to Simplify Business Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
urged its member states to reduce administrative burden imposed on
newly created enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"Improving and simplifying the business environment is the most
important priority, a view also shared by the European business
community," said EU Commissioner Christos Papoutsis, who is
responsible for enterprise policy.
</P>
<P>
Considering the job "a challenge for the member states," the
commissioner said the 15 EU member nations should exchange their
best practices in this field to benefit the whole community.
</P>
<P>
Papoutsis' proposal includes establishing a single contact
point for the registration of new enterprises and stimulating
businesses in their first years of development by alleviating
constraints of a tax, social, environmental and statistical nature.
</P>
<P>
Starting up a business in some EU member states can take a long
time due to the preliminary complicated procedures and a lack of
coordination between administrations. 
</P>
