<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rules on Overseas Project Financing Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning Commission
(SPC) and the State Administration of Foreign Exchange (SAFE)
issued "the Provisional Regulations on Administration of Project
Financing Overseas" here today.
</P>
<P>
The document is published in response to a recent State Council
decree to step up macro-control over borrowings of international
loans.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, a number of local governments and departments
have raised funds on foreign capital markets by means of project
financing, to build infrastructural projects, mainly some
Sino-foreign joint venture power plants, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
Lack of experience and understanding of the matter has led to
greater difficulties, higher cost of financing, and higher prices
of equipment imported for the projects. What's worse, some
departments have even guaranteed the payback of loans, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some financing efforts have been blocked due to lack
of efficient safety measures by the Chinese side, as foreign
banking institutions are hesitant to promise loans.
</P>
<P>
To solve the problems, the newly-published rule demands that
the overseas financing for domestic projects should be conducted
in a gradual and proper manner as project financing is more
complicated than corporate financing.
</P>
<P>
Project financing should only be allowed for infrastructural
projects, especially those that are foreign-funded and need
large-scale investment, have a strong capability to return the
loans, and have a long-term, stable income source.
</P>
<P>
These projects should require a total investment of 30 million
US dollars or more, and the financing of each project should be 15
million US dollars or more.
</P>
<P>
Projects without overseas investors should act slowly and
carefully when raising funds from abroad, as project financing
demands a stronger ability to repay the loans and carry out the
contract, and also the good reputation of the investors.
</P>
<P>
The regulations warn that the investors and other partners
involved in a project have different interests, and under certain
conditions these interests may conflict.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the rule says, the main investors of a project
should not be partners to carry out the contract of the project as
it may lead to serious problems.
</P>
<P>
Project financing has resulted in the increase of foreign debts
to the country, consequently, the proposals and feasibility
studies of such projects should be reported to SPC for approval,
and those of key projects should be approved by the State Council
via the SPC, according to the rule.
</P>
<P>
Financing projects should be approved or examined by the SAFE
to control the cost, ensure the cost-effects and the ability to
repay the loans, the rule says.
</P>
<P>
Localities should seriously control and guide local project
financing activities, especially the cost of financing and
construction, so as to make financing an effective way to utilize
overseas funds and ensure the state macro-control over foreign
debts, the regulations say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 15:16 </DATE_TIME>
