<HEADLINE> Top Chinese Shipping Firm Expands Overseas Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- COSCO Group, the largest shipping
contractor in China, has carried out a strategy of
internationalization and made great efforts to develop its
overseas business in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Its overseas business scope has been expanded from solely
playing the role of agent for foreign contractors to operating
overseas fleets, on-shore transport, storage, ports, tourism,
trade, real estate and restaurants.
</P>
<P>
These remarks were made by COSCO spokesman Gao Weijie at
today's news briefing to mark the group's 36th founding
anniversary. The China Ocean Shipping Company, the predecessor of
COSCO Group, was set up on April 27, 1961.
</P>
<P>
At present, Gao said, COSCO has 177 overseas firms with 5,000
employees. The group has set up a large business network covering
most of the countries in the world, with eight regional companies
as the pillars, he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1995 and 1996, COSCO successfully issued a total of 360
million US dollars of commercial bills in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, COSCO has sent more than 60,000 laborers to work for
foreign shipping firms and other industries. In 1996 alone, the
figure was 12,900.
</P>
<P>
COSCO's fleet includes nearly 600 vessels of various types with
its container and bulk cargo handling capacities ranking among the
world's largest. In 1996, the fleet shipped a total of 112 million
tons of goods. 
</P>
