<HEADLINE> HK Foreign Exchange Reserves Drop Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's foreign exchange
reserves as of the end of March were 63.4 billion US dollars,
dropping slightly from 63.8 billion US dollars a month ago,
according to an official release today.
</P>
<P>
The release said this excluded forward transactions yet to be
settled. Including forward transactions, the foreign reserves
reached 67.7 billion US dollars at end March, compared to 68.1
billion US dollars at end February.
</P>
<P>
It said the slight decrease in March from February represented
seasonal drawdowns in fiscal reserves and placements from the
Exchange Fund by the government and other institutions.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's foreign exchange reserves rank the seventh in the
world, according to the release.  
