<HEADLINE> Indonesians Urged to Make Election Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government today
again appealed to all Indonesians to make the general election on
May 29 a success.
</P>
<P>
Coordinating Minister for Political Affairs Soesilo Soedarman
said here after a meeting with several cabinet ministers and
high-ranking military officers that people have to try their best
to secure the smooth flow and peace and order of the election.
</P>
<P>
"It would be odd if Indonesians, being religious and civilized
and of noble character, could not make the election a success," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the government is determined to prevent any
conflict, big or small, as it could damage the campaign and
election.
</P>
<P>
The ruling party Golkar, the United Development Party and the
Indonesian Democratic Party are preparing for the forthcoming
election. They will officially start their campaign on April 27,
which will last until May 23.
</P>
<P>
The three political parties will vie for 425 of the 500 seats
in the House of the Representatives and the remaining 75 seats are
reserved for the armed forces, whose members do not vote.
</P>
<P>
More than 124 million Indonesians are eligible to vote in this
year's election, the seventh since the country's independence in
1945 and the sixth since the New Order administration led by
President Soeharto took office.
</P>
<P>
The Golkar has won all the five general elections since 1971.
</P>
