<HEADLINE> Chinese Inland City to Increase Use of Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The city of Nanping in east
China's coastal Fujian Province has set a goal of increasing
overseas economic cooperation to help local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Nanping plans to develop 200 foreign-funded enterprises this
year using overseas investment of about 250 million US dollars, a
nearly 14 percent rise over last year. It city also plans to set
up three enterprises aboard.
</P>
<P>
It expects to export 2.8 billion US dollars worth of goods this
year, earning 80 million US dollars in foreign exchange, a 12
percent increase over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The city is placing greater importance on opening-up the local
economy.
</P>
<P>
Nanping will put the majority of overseas investment into
transforming local state-owned enterprises and building
infrastructure, and into hi-tech, agricultural development,
tourism, and mining projects. 
