<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion to Miss World Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Olympic marathon champion
Josiah Thugwane will miss the World Athletics Championships in
Athends in August.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the squad in Johannesburg on Thursday, Athletics
South Africa (ASA) secretary general Banele Sindani said the
Olympic gold medallist had already said he did not want to compete
in order to allow 'unknowns' to run.
</P>
<P>
The 1992 Olympic 10,000 metres silver medalist Elana Meyer, who
was second behind Ethiopia's Olympic marathon champion Fatuma Roba
in the Boston marathon on Monday, has yet to decide whether she
will compete in the 5,000 or 10,000 meters events or the marathon
in Athens.
</P>
<P>
She has been provisionally included for the last two.
</P>
<P>
Colleen de Reuck, who finished one place behind Meyer in
Boston, told ASA earlier this month that she wanted to concentrate
on the 10,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
Sindani said the final line up would be announced as close to
the IAAF deadline of July 22 as possible and it was possible that
other athletes who performed well before then could be included.
</P>
<P>
The provisional squad is:
</P>
<P>
Men: Arnaud Malherbe (400m), Hezekiel Sepeng (800m), Marius
van Heerden (800m), Llewellyn Herbert (400m hurdles), Riaan Botha
(pole vault), Okkert Brits (pole vault), Burger Lambrecht (shot
put), Marius Corbett (javelin).
</P>
<P>
Women: Adri de Jongh (200 and 400m), Gwen Griffiths (1,500 and
5,000m), Colleen de Reuck (10,000m), Elana Meyer (10,000m).
</P>
<P>
Marathon squads:
</P>
<P>
Men: Lawrence Peu, Ezael Thlobo, Gert Thys, Xolile Yawa,
Martin Ndhiveni, Johannes Maremane, Abner Siphu, Adam Motlagale,
Nixon Nkodima, Able Mokibe.
