<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Model Worker Running Company To Aid Retirees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A retired Chinese model worker
is now running a company to earn money to give to his counterparts
whose pensions don't stretch far enough.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Chengzhe, 65, retired in 1992 from Shenyang Casting Plant
of Shenyang city in northeast China's Liaoning Province. He was a
national-level model worker in the 1950s, and was responsible for
nearly 1,000 technical inventions which helped make or save more
than 10 million yuan over the past 40 years.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after he retired, he opened his brainchild, the
Chengzhe Model Worker Industrial Company, employed more than 7,000
other retired model workers, and now is able to return to society
the overwhelming majority of the firm's profit.
</P>
<P>
Many of the retirees who work for Zhang are in financial
trouble due to the rise in living expenses. Through his company,
Zhang provides subsidies for his workers and gives jobs to their
children.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yuxiang, a retired model worker who suffers from uremia,
couldn't afford her medical treatment. Zhang visited her many
times in hospital and paid her medical costs.
</P>
<P>
During Spring festivals, Zhang took gifts and money to the
widow of another model worker. "I have been taken good care of
over the past more than 30 years since my husband passed away,"
the widow said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, a plainly dressed man, retains his humble lifestyle. "I
will spend all the money the company earns to ensure the retired
model workers a happy life in their remaining years," he said.
</P>
<P>
The company has set up an orthopedics clinic for the old, and
plans to open a full-service hospital.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's philanthropy has won praise and support from his
community and the local government, and more people are joining
his efforts to lend a hand to the needy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
