<HEADLINE> Car Rental Industry Booming in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- With more and more Beijingers
renting cars for weekend road trips, the number of car rental
companies in the Chinese capital has soared to 170, more than
quadruple the figure of 1996.
</P>
<P>
And the popular rent-a-car firms in Beijing last year scored a
total of 240 million yuan (29 million US dollars) in business
volume.
</P>
<P>
To rent a car, a customer must present a valid identity card,
residence certificate and drivers licence, and pay a cash deposit.
</P>
<P>
The companies will do annual vehicle maintenance checks and
provide auto insurance, and offer round-the-clock emergency repair
service for the customers.
</P>
<P>
Most of the companies can keep 70 to 80 percent of their cars
rented out. During weekends and holidays, the companies often
don't have enough cars to meet the demand. 
</P>
