determined to boost their relations in all spheres, a statement
issued following an official visit to by Italian Prime Minister
Romano Prodi said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of Kuwaiti Crown Prince and
Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah, said the
two sides agreed to form a joint committee to be chaired by the
foreign ministers of both countries for consultations on a wide
range of issues of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
