<HEADLINE> COSCO Calls For A Stable Int'l Shipping Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- COSCO Group, China's flag carrier
for the shipping industry, today marked the 36th anniversary of
its founding by asking for better cooperation between all shipping
contractors in the world to stablize the sector internationally.
</P>
<P>
The call was made here at a news conference for the event,
which was attended by several COSCO leading officials.
</P>
<P>
COSCO officials also asked all shipping firms to compete in a
fair and equal manner, and with mutual trust and improved
cooperation, to maintain a sustained and healthy development of
the industry.
</P>
<P>
The group holds that to compete for market share by cutting
prices will only lead to an unreasonably low price level, mutual
distrust among contractors and disorder in the shipping market,
which is harmful to the entire industry.
</P>
<P>
The officials urged business rivals to improve service and
management, and said that when shipping companies readjust their
regular lines, they should take care not to disturb the balance of
the industry.
</P>
<P>
The leading Chinese shipping firm also asked that hotlines be
set up between major contractors for the purpose of stablizing the
industry.
</P>
<P>
They said COSCO further advocates that outdated ships should be
dismantled, and that environmental protection of seas and oceans
should be a major concern for the industry.
</P>
<P>
At the briefing, COSCO spokesman Gao Weijie told a group of
local journalists that the company was founded in 1961 and now
owns nearly 600 vessels of various types with a total of 17
million dwt.
</P>
<P>
In 1995 and 1996, COSCO's vessels transported 117 million tons
and 112 million tons of goods respectively.
</P>
<P>
Gao said that the Chinese shipping firm will compete with its
advantages and quality service, and will strive to standardize the
international shipping market and curb unfair competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
