<P>
Another Argentine team Velez Sarsfield, which won the cup in
1994, drew 0-0 away to Sporting Cristal of Peru.
</P>
<P>
Gremio was reduced to 10 men after a player was sent off in the
match in Asuncion, where Guarani won on goals by Hugo Ovelar in
the fourth and 82nd minutes.
</P>
<P>
River Plate twice trailed in their game and then led 3-2 before
settling for a draw against the team coached by Alfio Basile,
Argentina's 1994 World Cup coach.
</P>
<P>
Five of the goals came in a dramatic first half before Claudio
Ubeda salvaged a draw for Racing 12 minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
In the other ties played Wednesday, Bolivar of Bolivia drew 1-1
away to Minerven of Venezuela while Millonarios of Colombia beat
Uruguay's five-times winner Penarol 2-0 in Bogota. 
</P>
</TEXT>
