<HEADLINE> 1997 RAC Rally to be Shortest Ever </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The course of RAC Rally this year
will be the shortest route in the event's history, it was revealed
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
But the organisers insist that the rally, which has been
re-instated as a World Championship event, has lost none of the
qualities which make it one of the most challenging courses on the
world circuit.
</P>
<P>
In a major departure from last year's route, the event, spread
over three days from November 23-25, will omit the gruelling
Kielder Forest section in the Scottish Borders which claimed many
leading contenders in 1996.
</P>
<P>
This year's forest stages will take place on the final leg in
South Wales on roads which have not been used by an international
rally for a decade. 
</P>
