<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong Bank announced
today that it will donate 25 million HK dollars (3.2 million U.S.
dollars) to the China Charity Federation (CCF) to help the needy.
</P>
<P>
The money will be paid at an estimated 2.5 million HK dollars
(320,000 U.S. dollars) a year through the Hongkong Bank Foundation
China Charity Federation Fund, which has been established for the
purpose.
</P>
<P>
A proportion of the fund's first income will be used for
training staff, said Cui Naifu, chairman of the CCF, at today's
donation ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The CCF, a national charity organization, aims to raise funds
for various welfare programs to help people in poverty and crisis.
Founded in 1994, the CCF now has 59 institutional members in 25
cities and provinces throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Bank Chairman John Strickland said: "In this historic
year in which China resumes sovereignty over Hong Kong, it is
entirely appropriate that we should extend our support to the
charitable organization in China."
</P>
<P>
This largest bank in Hong Kong also made a donation of the same
amount to the Community Chest today, which pools funds for social
welfare agencies in assistance to the needy in the Hong Kong
community.  
</P>
