<HEADLINE> Nepali Youth Team to Climb Mt. Qomolangma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Five Nepali youths are to leave
here to climb Mt. Qomolangma through the south face to mark the
forthcoming 14th World Youth and Student Festival in Cuba, a youth
organization announced today.
</P>
<P>
All the five members of the Qomolangma expedition are below the
age of 35 and have experiences climbing mountains above 8,000
meters, according to the Democratic National Youth Federation of
Nepal, which sponsored and organized the expedition.
</P>
<P>
The climbing team is going to leave Kathmandu Saturday and set
up the base camp at a 5,500-meter-high next week, organizers told
a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The climbers, one of them had successfully climbed
Mt. Qomolangma before, will probably make their final ascent to
the summit in mid-May.
</P>
<P>
The team will establish only three camps including the base
camp before they launch assaults to the 8,848-meter-high summit,
organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Normally Mt. Qomolangma climbers establish four to five camps
during their expedition through the south route on Nepal side.
</P>
<P>
The Qomolangma expedition is organized to show Nepali youths'
commitment to world peace and mark the 14th World Youth and
Student Festival, which is to be held in Havana, Cuba, in July
this year, organizers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
