<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Marginally Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The combination of options
expiries and the upcoming holiday long weekend kept the Australian
share market fairly subdued today.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries index closed 2.4 points firmer at 2474.7,
from an intraday high of 2480.2.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index closed 3.5 points up at 3894.8 while
the All Resources index added 1.5 points to reach 1379.3.
</P>
<P>
Lance Jones broker Hamish Dee said one of the best performing
stocks of the day was Coca-Cola Amatil, which picked up 47.7
cents, or 3.24 percent, in the session.
</P>
<P>
The shares of Coca-Cola have increased 27 percent since the
company announced on April 3 its planned merger with the
Philippines-listed San Miguel Corp's bottling unit.
</P>
<P>
The banking index closed 1.3 points down at 4259.6, with ANZ
recording the biggest fall of 9 cents, while National Australia
Bank was 2.6 cents firmer and Westpac Bank and the Commonwealth
Bank gained 3 cents each.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 305.76 million shares valued at
803.82 million Australian dollars (622.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
