Iraqi-Turkish border sees daily the arrival of trucks loaded with
food contracted for with Turkish companies.
</P>
<P>
He expected many ships carrying food to anchor shortly in the
Umm Qasr port.
</P>
<P>
The oil-for-food agreement between Iraq and the United Nations
allows Iraq to sell 2 billion U.S. dollars worth of oil over six
months to buy food and other supplies for its people hit hard by
the U.N. sanctions. 
