<HEADLINE> Macao Police Launch Action Against Increasing Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Macao dispatched more than 400
policemen for a major joint action against rising crimes in the
territory, detaining two suspects and 16 illegal immigrants
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The action was jointly launched by several departments of
security, commanded by the Police Action Coordination Center. It
was the largest action in eight years.
</P>
<P>
Security forces, armed police, maritime police and judiciary
police, aided by a dozen police dogs, raided a slum-area suspected
to be hideout for more than three hours from five o'clock early
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
A total of 16 illegal immigrants and two suspects of recent
robbery and other cases were detained. Police also found equipment
of acoustic systems and video-surveillance systems.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the center told local press Wednesday that the
action is "aimed at the rising serious crimes over the past
weeks," adding that all departments concerned will continue to
cooperate well in action to maintain social order and public
security.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the spokesman said more plainclothes policemen
have been deployed in the street to increase patrol.
</P>
<P>
A wave of robbery, shooting and killing cases occurred in the
territory over the past weeks, reportedly related to triad
fighting for interests in casinos. 
</P>
