<HEADLINE> Mozambican Opposition Party to Join Local </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Opposition Mozambique National
Resistance (RENAMO) leader Afonso Dhlakama has pledged that his
party will participate in the local elections set for November,
the Noticias newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
However, he expressed concern about the financial troubles
from which the biggest opposition party is suffering when
returning here from his seven-day visit to Germany last night.
</P>
<P>
The RENAMO owed debts during the 1994 elections and the then
international community had committed to helping pay the debts,
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he had mentioned it to the German government which
promised to inform the EU member states of the problem.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, RENAMO parliamental leader Raul Domingos said in an
interview with BBC that the RENAMO does not rule out the
possibility of boycotting the November elections. 
</P>
