<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Finds Arms in Liberia Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The West African peace-keeping
force in Liberia known as ECOMOG has discovered a large quantity
of hidden arms at the country's border with Ivory Coast, a report
reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG Commander Victor Malu was quoted as saying on Wednesday
that the arms were found in the area formerly controlled by the
National Patriotic Front of Liberia led by Charles Taylor, who is
widely regarded as one of the most hopeful presidential candidate
in the May 30 elections.
</P>
<P>
Among the arms discovered were large quantities of bombs and
ammunitions, anti-aircraft guns, 105 mm guns and anti-tank guns
and motors, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Malu said his force is still interrogating the persons found
carrying the weapons, and that once enough information is
gathered, Taylor would be called for questioning.
</P>
<P>
The commander declined to mention what action he would take if
Taylor is eventually implicated, but said that the situation
would not be a threat to the peace process.
</P>
<P>
After the January 31 deadline for Liberian faction fighters to
surrenders their arms, the peace-keepers in early March found several
trucks of arms in the house of Alhaji Kromah, the leader of the United
Liberation Movement.
</P>
<P>
Kromah was first arrested and was to be prosecuted but was later
pardoned by the ECOMOG for the continuance of the peace process.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets International Celebrities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met here
today with former Canadian Prime Minister Martin Brian Mulroney,
former US Secretary of State George Shultz, and other
international dignitaries from North America, Western Europe, and
the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
These dignitaries are here in China to attend the second
session of the China International Trust and Investment
Corp. (CITIC) International Advisory Council, which was held here
today.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome, Li expressed his appreciation for their
opinions and suggestions on China's economic development,
infrastructure construction, and financial reform.
</P>
<P>
Li said that during the past years, they have made valuable
efforts and positive contributions to promoting the friendly
relations between their countries and China.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China appreciates their attention now, as in the
past, to China's economic development and social progress, and
their active participation in economic and trade cooperation and
exchanges with China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li attributed China's economic success in
the past few years to firmly exercising macro-economic control,
effective implementation of a relatively tight financial policy,
and achieving a balance between total supply and demand.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government welcomes overseas investment, he said,
adding that China will further step up its reform and opening
still wider to the outside world, and continue its friendly
cooperation with other countries on an equal and mutually
beneficial basis.
</P>
<P>
On Hong Kong's economic prospects, Li said that after Hong Kong
returns to the motherland, its economy will keep its rising
momentum, and and it will maintain long-term prosperity and
stability.
</P>
<P>
He added that the rapid economic development in China's inland
areas will add vigor to Hong Kong's economy.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Hong Kong, in accordance with the principle
of "one country, two systems," will practice "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and enjoy a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong's development potentials will be better
explored, and its tomorrow will be much better than today.
</P>
<P>
The visitors said that China's vigorous economic development
left them with a deep impression.
</P>
<P>
Mulroney said that he is confident in Hong Kong's prosperity
and stability.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on international issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
CITIC, established in 1979, has become a comprehensive
transnational industrial group. The CITIC International Advisory
Council was set up in 1995 to bring about further expansion of
business, and 13 international figures such as Mulroney and Shultz
were invited to be members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
