<HEADLINE> China to Hold Third Agricultural Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The third national agricultural
exhibition in China will be held in Beijing between October 21 and
27 this year.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Liu Chengguo, Chinese vice-minister of
Agriculture, at a news conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be organized by the Ministry of Agriculture
with the assistance of five other central government departments
and the Beijing Municipal People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Highlighted with the theme of "Industrialization and
Agro-science," the exhibition will display new results and
products in the fields of agriculture, animal husbandry, fishery,
rural industry, and farm machinery.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will have three new qualities:
</P>
<P>
-- It will feature the main theme by holding a picture show on
the role and achievements of agricultural industrialization in the
entrance hall.
</P>
<P>
-- Two halls will be added to the exhibition compared with the
previous sessions with the total floor space expanding to 50,000
sq. m. Participants will include 30 delegations from all parts of
China, eight special delegations and companies from Hong Kong,
Macao, and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
-- Emphasis will be given to technical exchanges and trade
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Two national agricultural exhibitions have been held since
1992. The second one presented 2,000 prize-awarding products,
racking up a transaction value of five billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
