<HEADLINE> Downturn in German Inflation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Federal Statistics Office in
Wiesbaden today reported a downward trend in Germany's inflation,
saying the annual inflation rate for April would decline to 1.4
percent from the March level of 1.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The cost of living for western German households fell 0.1
percent from March, said the office in a preliminary report based
on data from four key western German states.
</P>
<P>
The final price data for April will be issued around mid-May.
</P>
