<HEADLINE> China to Hold National Fair for International Investment and Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- On September 8th, China will
begin holding an annual fair for international investment and
trade in Xiamen, a port city in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The China Fair for International Investment and Trade (CFIIT),
is the only nationwide investment promotion activity focusing on
foreign direct investment, according to Sun Zhenyu, Chinese
vice-minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
The CFIIT, sponsored by MOFTEC, will focus on attracting
investment from global sources and trading products manufactured
by foreign-funded enterprises, Sun added.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the convening of the fair is aimed at exercising
correct guidance and working out unified and standardized measures
for various trade and investment promotion talks held in China, to
improve the efficiency of the introduction of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
During the fair that was upgraded from the 10-year-old Fujian
Fair for International Investment and Trade, a commodity show for
businesses across the Taiwan Straits will be held.
</P>
<P>
Till now, nearly 40 Chinese provinces, cities, and ministries
have registered for the first CFIIT, which will be held from
September 8 to 13. The participants have provided over 1,000
projects for foreign investment and a large volume of orders for
commodities. Over 2,000 businesses from Taiwan have also applied
for the commodity show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
