<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Court to Expand Ties with Hong Kong Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Exchanges between the
Intermediate People's Court of Shenzhen and the courts in Hong
Kong will surely increase after Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, a senior judge in Shenzhen City, Guangdong Province,
said today.
</P>
<P>
Xu Liangdong, president of the Shenzhen court, said that in
1996 the court dealt with 399 cases related with foreigners and
residents from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan, a rise of 210 percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Among the cases, 365 were related with people from Hong Kong,
Macao, and Taiwan, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
Bordering on Hong Kong, Shenzhen is a special economic zone
where flexible policies to encourage investors from Hong Kong,
Macao and overseas.
</P>
<P>
China has been exerting efforts to deal with overseas-related
cases in strict accordance with international treaties and
conventions, and to protect the interests of investors, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen court will continue to promote Shenzhen's
economic, trade, and cultural ties with Hong Kong, Macao, and
Taiwan in accordance with the "one country, two systems"
principle, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
