<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Becomes China's Large Flower Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's "Northern garden",
Shangdong province, has become the country's major flower
producer, with its 600 types of cultivated flowers and 400 types
of wildflowers, according to a national meeting on flower
industry, which was held recently in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shandong is on the lower reaches of the Yellow River in east
China, near the East Sea, and one of the birthplaces of China's
ancient culture.
</P>
<P>
Its flower industry has flourished since 1990, and today the
province cultivates 6,000 hectares of flowers, worth 71.4 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
It has six flower production bases, including a peony base in
Heze, a Chinese rose base in Weifang, a rose base in Pingyin, and
a pomegranate base in Zaozhuang. It has 20 wholesale flower
markets, over 400 flower shops, 1,100 enterprises in the flower
industry employing 500,000 people, and over 9,000 villages
specializing in flower cultivation.
</P>
<P>
The Qingzhou Wanhua Flower Company is the largest flower
production enterprise and distributing center north of the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
Shao Guifang, honorary director of Shandong flower association
says that the province will combine its flower industry with a
more beautiful environment, cultivate 13,000 hectares of flowers
worth 350 million US dollars, and make the flower industry
Shandong's pillar industry.
</P>
<P>
The flower industry was estimated to worth more than 120
million US dollars in business in 1996, with exports going to
other countries in Asia, and to Europe and America.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Famine Worsens in N. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Famine situation is aggravating
in Kitgum District, northern Uganda, the New Vision reported
today.
</P>
<P>
James Oryem Canogura, the assistant resident district
councillor, said the worsening situation may lead to mass
starvation if no urgent food supply was available.
</P>
<P>
Some sub-county local chief in the district confirmed the
claim of Canogura.
</P>
<P>
Villagers have left their homes for towns to earn money to
support their families, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The government and some non-government organizations are
managing to provide the district with relief food, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
There are some 52,000 displaced people in the camps in the
district.
</P>
<P>
Some residents told the newspaper that many people have not
started cultivation in this rain season due to lack of hand hoes.
</P>
<P>
Kitgum was hit by drought during last dry season from late
last November to late last March. The situation was aggravating
by the rebellion in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
