<HEADLINE> Two Key Rebels Surrender to Government in Sierra </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Two top members of the rebel
Revolutionary United Front (RUF) which has fought with the Sierra
leone authorities since 1991, have surrendered to the government,
official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Timothy Serry, chief bodyguard to disputed leader Foday
Sankoh, flew into the capital from Abidjan two days ago.
</P>
<P>
State House sources said it took weeks of persuasion for Serry
to accept the government invitation to give himself up. Special
security adviser to president Tejan Kabbah confirmed the news to
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"It's true. Every day we hear of RUF men and women defecting,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
According to diplomatic sources, Serry spent three weeks in
the Sierra Leone Consulate in Abidjan.
</P>
<P>
Ibrahim Barrie, a former escort to Sankoh, surrendered to
tribal authorities on Wednesday in Tonkolili in the north of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mansaray confirmed that the RUF officials seized by
a break-away group of the organization "are well", saying "we
have gone far with negotiations with RUF commandos in the field
for their release." 
</P>
