<HEADLINE> Pak, China Sign Implementation Program of Cultural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The existing Pak-China friendly
relations are to be further strengthened with the signing today of
the Implementation Program of the Cultural Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Implementation Program of the Cultural Agreement between
Pakistan and China for 1997-1999 was signed here today by Akhtar
Hassan Khan, secretary of the Culture Ministry, and Zhang Chengli,
Chinese ambassador to Pakistan, on behalf of their respective
governments.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and China signed the Cultural Agreement on March 26,
1965. The Implementation Program for the next three years includes
exchanges of cultural troupes, visiting scholars, exhibitions of
folk arts and crafts and photographs of folk life, scientific
books and sports.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Khan told Xinhua after signing the Implementation
Program, "Pak-China relations are extremely cordial and friendly.
China is Pakistan's best neighbor in the world."
</P>
<P>
Cultural exchanges have been the major content in the
Pak-Chinese relationship. Therefore, the signing of the
Implementation Program of the Cultural Agreement is of great
importance and will further cement the ties between the two
countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Zhang said on the occasion that China and Pakistan
are two close and friendly neighbors, which are both ancient
civilized nations in the Orient.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the effective and successful
implementation of the Implementation Program will certainly
promote better understanding between the two peoples.  
</P>
</TEXT>
