<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index declined by another 14.63 points to close at 2020.17 today,
the lowest level in more than two years.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 107.97 million units, valued
at 361.51 million Singapore dollars (about 251.05 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 250 to 60 while 310
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
posted a turnover of 7.38 million units. It was followed by
HaiSunHup Right which had 4.52 million units traded. The Kuala
Lumpur Industries was next with 3.87 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led the gainers of the day as it rose by 70 cents
to finish at 20.3 Singapore dollars. Asia Pacific gained 35 cents
to end at 7 dollars while Elec closed 24 cents higher at 5.2 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Keppel Corporation was the biggest loser
as it slid by 1.85 Singapore dollars to end at 6.8 Singapore
dollars. Its warrant 97 fell by 57 cents to close at 2 Singapore
dollars while the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign, the
Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign and the United
Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign dropped by 50 cents to finish at 17,
17 and 14.2 Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
