<HEADLINE> Radio Programs Introducing Shaanxi to Overseas Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A six-month radio program
designed to introduce northwest China's Shaanxi Province to
overseas audiences came to a close, with six foreign nationals
winning special awards for answering feedback questions.
</P>
<P>
Sources from China Radio International (CRI) said that they had
substantial coverage on subjects ranging from the northwest China
province's reform and opening-up drive, economic growth,
investment environment, and tourist resources to history and
culture, and broadcasted the news in 43 overseas languages.
</P>
<P>
The program, which began last September with full support from
the Shaanxi Provincial Government, lasted a total of 400 hours.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of last February, CRI had collected as many as
259,880 answer sheets from 155 countries and regions in the world,
setting a record in the radio service's history in launching
feedback radio programs.
</P>
<P>
The six winners who were given special awards are from Canada,
Spain, Japan, the Philippines, Tanzania, and Nepal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
