<HEADLINE> Guangxi Preparing for Flood Prevention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in southwest China is making preparations for flood
prevention to ensure a good harvest this year.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Kejie, chairman of the regional government, said that
five tasks should be in local leaders' agendas: reinforcing
dangerous dykes and dams; clearing away obstacles in rivers and
lakes; making preparations for the distribution of building
materials; forecasting floods; and improving the work to direct
flood prevention.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi suffered flood and drought disasters in 1988, 1995, and
1996, with direct economic losses estimated at 60 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region has now put water conservancy construction as the
first priority of all infrastructure facilities. Since 1996, the
whole region has spent nearly 500 million yuan on water
conservancy construction. 
</P>
