<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five-Nation Accord Hailed As Unprecedented Achievement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The presidents of China, Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan today hailed the agreement
on border arms reduction between the five countries as "an
unprecedented achievement."
</P>
<P>
In separate speeches delivered after the signing of the accord
in the Kremlin, the presidents unanimously extolled the document
as of historic significance to security and stability in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, a result of over seven years of negotiations,
provides detailed measures to reduce military forces and armaments
within a depth of 100 kilometers from the border lines between
China and the other four countries which share a 7,000 kilometer
long border.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said in his speech that the
signing of the accord conduces to maintaining peace, stability and
tranquillity in the border areas and facilitating further growth
of good-neighborly relations, friendship, mutual trust on the
basis of equality and mutually-beneficial cooperation between the
five countries.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, it "offers a security model different from the
Cold-War mentality in safeguarding peace, security and stability
in the Asia Pacific region and the world at large, thereby opening
up a useful way for the enhancement of mutual trust among the
states," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin said that thanks to the
brand-new atmosphere between the five countries, they have been
able to discuss and tackle in real earnest all the most
complicated problems to formulate the unique document.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of the accord will consolidate mutual trust
among all parties and exert positive impact on the relations
between them, Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
President Nursultan Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan said that the
agreement will be a factor to enhance stability and trust in the
region and promote peace and friendship between the five countries.
</P>
<P>
The document is oriented toward the 21st century and will be
recorded in the history of world politics, Nazarbayev said.
</P>
<P>
President Askar Akayev of Kyrgyzstan set a high value on the
accord and described it as a proper one of historic and political
importance.
</P>
<P>
Top leaders of the five countries have established a fresh
basis of international law in the field of military cooperation
and made great contribution to setting up the framework of
security and stability in the Asia Pacific region, Akayev said.
</P>
<P>
President Emomali Rakhmonov of Tajikistan regarded the signing
of the document as an important event in the irreversible process
of building up trust and stability in the border areas between
China and the four countries.
</P>
<P>
The accord, together with the agreement on confidence building
in the military field in border areas between the five countries
reached a year ago, will help solve the remaining problems in
fixing border lines between China and the four countries,
Rakhmonov said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
