<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Providing Large Loans For Railway Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's State Development Bank
has provided a total of 32.8 billion yuan in loans for railway
projects over the past three years, accounting for 12 percent of
the country's total amount of loans in Renminbi.
</P>
<P>
The funds were used for 49 large and medium-sized programs,
including the Beijing-Kowloon, Baoji-Zhongwei, and Nanning-Kunming
railway lines, China Business Times reports.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, loans for railway projects
amounted to 2.2 billion yuan, and the figure is expected to reach
11.7 billion yuan by the year's end, bank sources say.
</P>
<P>
During the first three years of the country's Eighth Five-Year
Plan (1991-95), only 5.45 billion yuan in loans went to railways,
far less than those made by the State Development Bank alone,
which was founded three years ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
