<HEADLINE> Pakistan Considers Approving Weapons Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The question of Pakistan's
ratification of the Chemical Weapons Convention (CWC) is under
active consideration by the government, a Foreign Office spokesman
said today.
</P>
<P>
However, it is necessary that all the preparatory work relating
to this convention including documentation of the entire chemical
and allied industry in Pakistan be completed, the spokesman said
at a press briefing here.
</P>
<P>
"We are in the process of taking steps in this direction," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's decision to ratify the CWC will also be guided by
the position of the rest of the international community, in
particular those states that possess chemical weapons as well as
those in possession of other weapons of mass destruction, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Pakistan is a signatory to the CWC and subscribes
to its objectives of promoting disarmament and non-proliferation
of chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
And Pakistan has always been an ardent advocate of a complete
ban on the development, production, stockpiling and use of
chemical weapons, he said.
</P>
<P>
The use of chemical agents for the purposes of warfare has
never figured in Pakistan's defense doctrines, the spokesman
declared.  
</P>
</TEXT>
