<HEADLINE> China Modernizes Its Military Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China has intensified its efforts
to modernize its naval bases through large-scale technological
renovation.
</P>
<P>
Docks and protective fences as well as water-, power- and
heat-supply facilities have been renovated and upgraded in the
ports of Qingdao, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Zhanjiang.
</P>
<P>
Military ports in Lushun, Zhoushan, Wenzhou and Sanya cities
have been restructured in a more rational way and each of the
ports are now divided into different quaters for various purposes,
including anchoring, living, logistics and recreation.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection has been highlighted in these
ports. Since 1985, environmental monitoring stations have been set
up in 18 military ports responsible for overall supervision of
waste-discharge. 
</P>
