<HEADLINE> Short Time, Big Profit for PICC Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- PICC Life, a subsidiary of the
People's Insurance Company of China (PICC), sold 900 million
yuan-worth of life insurance policies during a 45-day nationwide sales
campaign from January 1 to February 15.
</P>
<P>
He Jiesheng, president of PICC Life, declared the success as a
milestone for her company, which aims to quadruple its total
premium income in the year 2000 compared to 1995, to reach 71
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
She said the company had 80,000 sales agents as of February 15,
in addition to 40,000 other employees.
</P>
<P>
PICC Life, reshaped into limited-liability company in 1996 from
the former life insurance department of the PICC, is the country's
largest life insurer. Its sales agent system was introduced last
year.
</P>
<P>
The insurance sales agent system was first introduced to China
by AIG (American International Group) when it started sales of
life insurance services in Shanghai years ago.
</P>
<P>
Insurance specialists say that China's life insurance market
will keep expanding in the coming years with the stable growth of
the country's economy and the rising annual income of Chinese
residents.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the competition among life insurers in China's
market will become tough, they say.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yongwei, president of PICC, said that PICC will become an
international insurance group capable of stimulating the
development of the national insurance industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
