<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Imposes Anti-dumping Duties On EU, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today announced it
has imposed anti-dumping duties on manufacturers of self copy
paper from European Union (EU) and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The anti-dumping duties were imposed after final investigation
showed continued dumping of the products materially injured the
domestic industry, the Ministry of International Trade and
Industry said in a statement here today.
</P>
<P>
The rates of the duties imposed on the manufacturers from the
EU ranged from between four to nine percent while a rate of 23
percent is imposed on all manufacturers of self copy paper from
Indonesia, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
However, anti-dumping duties are not applicable on French
company, Papetries Mougeot, and two Indonesian companies, P.T.
Parisindo Pratama and P.T. Pabrik Kertas Tjiwi Kimia, which were
found not to be dumping the products concerned into Malaysia, it
added.
</P>
<P>
The EU companies on which the anti-dumping duties were imposed
are Arjo Wiggins Carbonless Paper Int Ltd., UK (11 percent),
Copigraph S.A., France (nine percent), Stora Carbonless Paper
GmbH, Germany (seven percent), Torraspapel S.A., Spain (four
percent), and 11 percent anti-dumping duties are imposed on other
manufacturers from EU, it said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the Royal Customs and Excise Department will
enforce the collection of the anti-dumping duties.
</P>
<P>
"This final measure shall be effective for not more than five
years from the date the government gazettes the final
determination of the investigation, that is, April 20, 1997," it
said.
</P>
<P>
The investigation into the dumping of self copy paper into
Malaysia was conducted following a joint petition lodged on August
12 last year by Gamuda Paper Industries Sdn Bhd (Private Ltd.) and
Ann Bee (M) Sdn Bhd (Private Ltd.), on behalf of the domestic
industry. They requested that anti-dumping measures be imposed on
self copy paper imported from the EU and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation initiated on August 22 following
the petition found that the domestic industry had suffered
material injury as a result of the dumping practice and
provisional anti-dumping duties, in the form of bank guarantees,
were imposed on the affected manufacturers last November.
</P>
<P>
The rates of duties imposed ranged between nine percent to 26
percent for manufacturers from EU and between 23 percent to 39
percent for those from Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
After the provisional anti-dumping duties were imposed, the
second stage of investigation on the petition started, which
confirmed that dumping still continues and the domestic industry
is materially injured by the practice, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
