<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, Bangladesh, Thailand, India to Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka, India, Thailand and
Bangladesh have agreed in principle to form a new economic
grouping to strengthen the four countries' economic cooperation,
according to informed sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the idea was raised by Thai Foreign
Minister Prachuab Chaiyasan at a meeting with Indian officials
during his stay in New Delhi recently.
</P>
<P>
Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Pitak Intrawityanunt proposed the
same idea when he visited Bangladesh this week.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that senior officials from the four countries
will next month discuss details of a pact to form the economic
grouping.
</P>
<P>
They also said that the Asian Development Bank is conducting a
study on the proposal grouping.
</P>
<P>
After the grouping is formed, the four countries would be able
to enhance cooperation in various fields, such as agriculture,
technology, transport, fishery and investment, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
