<HEADLINE> 28 Killed, 29 Injured in Traffic Accidents in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-eight people were killed
and 29 others injured in several traffic accidents in Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that a car collided with a truck in Havza town
of Samsun along the Black Sea of Turkey today, killing eight
people, including three children.
</P>
<P>
In another development this morning, one car collided with a
truck in Giresun along the Black Sea, killing six people,
including four Georgians.
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed today and 20 others injured when a car
collided with a passenger bus and later another passenger bus
from opposite side hit the two vehicles in Ankara, capital of
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three Turks were killed today when a truck
collided with a car in Uzundere town of Erzurum province,
eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The agency also said that six pilgrims were killed late
Wednesday night and nine others injured when a bus carrying
pilgrims fell into a 50-meter-deep abyss in Belen town of Hatay
province linking neighboring Syria.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the brake of the bus, which returned
from pilgrimage in Mecca, Saudi Arabia, exploded in the region,
killing five pilgrims and injuring 10 others immediately. But
one more pilgrim died later in hospital, said the agency.
</P>
</TEXT>
