<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province To Develop IT Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin
Province intends to turn its information technology (IT) sector
into a leading industry by the year 2000 and expects to draw from
it more than 10 billion yuan in annual output value.
</P>
<P>
The province will focus on telecommunications, computers,
electronic components, appliances, liquid crystal display
technology, automobile electronics, and optics.
</P>
<P>
The province has 18 large and mid-sized electronics enterprises
making more than 200 IT-related products, such as TV sets, cables,
rare-earth magnetic materials, program-controlled switchboards,
and floppy disks.
</P>
<P>
It has set up three IT research centers and three product
development centers to help bost the information industry. In the
past five years, it has set up bases for development of
semiconductors, components, and rare-earth magnetic materials.
</P>
<P>
A five-billion-yuan color liquid crystal display project is
scheduled for the 1996-2000 period, and is expected to be one of
the largest of its kind in north China. The province is looking
for overseas investors to jointly develop the project.
</P>
<P>
The province has introduced overseas funds and technology for a
large-scale improvement of the local IT industry so as to help
some of its products reach international standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
