<HEADLINE> South China Region to Speed Up Road Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region intends to extend its highways to 47,000 km by
the turn of the century, to further the local transportation
network.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1995 period, the region poured six billion yuan
into local highway construction, stretching local highways to
41,344 km.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the region invested more than 3.2 billion yuan into
local road construction, adding 1,500 km of highways and nine
bridges.
</P>
<P>
As a result, a local highway network linking with southwest
Yunnan and Guizhou Provinces, and Vietnam has been partially
constructed.
</P>
<P>
This year Guangxi will focus on the construction of highways
linking the northern and southern parts of the region, and build
5,000 km of roads in the region's west poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
More efforts in the coming years will also be placed on
building the part of the highway within Guangxi which links the
neighboring coatal city of Zhanjiang in the south with Chongqing
Municipality up in the north, in addition to the part of the
highway linking its capital city of Nanning with Hengyang in
central Hunan Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
