<HEADLINE> Zambian Copper Conglomerate Suffers From Fuel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The copper production of the
Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM) was expected to fall by
9,457 tons in April from an early official estimate of 27,057
tons due to a critical fuel shortage.
</P>
<P>
"The shortfall is largely on account of the shortage of heavy
fuel oil due to low supplies from Indeni (the oil company which
supplies fuel to the conglomerate)," said the ZCCM monthly
production report available here today.
</P>
<P>
The fuel crisis forced ZCCM to shut down Nkana and Mufulira
smelters in March and April. The Mufulira smelter was closed from
March 28 to April 12 and furnaces at the Nkana smelter were
switched off from March 28 to April 16.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the production of the conglomerate is projected
at 17,600 tons for April.
</P>
<P>
However, the ZCCM report did not reveal why Indeni reduced the
fuel supply. 
</P>
</TEXT>
