The five stations, which will be complicated in design and
difficult to build, pose a challenge to both domestic and overseas
manufacturers, according to some local experts.
</P>
<P>
The hydraulic project is meant to supply water to major
industrial bases in Shanxi Province in north China.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500 million US dollars of overseas loans will be
used by the project, including 400 million US dollars from the
World Bank in fiscal 1997.
</P>
<P>
It is leraned that many domestic and overseas manufacturers
have shown great interest in the project. 
