<HEADLINE> Asia-Europe Expert Meeting Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Europe Expert Meeting on
Technological Cooperation opened here today with an attendance of
some 100 representatives from the 26 members of the Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM).
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting, originally proposed by Chinese Premier Li
Peng at the first ASEM in Bangkok in March 1996, was endorsed by
the ASEM leaders as a follow-up activity of the ASEM.
</P>
<P>
Li said in a letter to the expert meeting that the Chinese
government places high priority on the role that science and
technology play in the country's economic growth. He said that
China is willing to conduct multilateral and bilateral cooperation
and exchanges in science and technology with Asian and European
countries on a basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
He wishes that the current expert meeting on technological
cooperation will add more substance to the new partnership of Asia
and Europe and contribute to the promotion of cooperation between
the two sides.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor and Minister in charge of the State Science and
Technology Commission Song Jian said at the opening ceremony of
the meeting that the mutual beneficial cooperation between Asia
and Europe in the fields of science and technology is of great
significance for the economic development of every country in the
two regions.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys of the European Union (EU) and Singapore
residing in China also spoke at the meeting's opening ceremony.
</P>
</TEXT>
