<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 07:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader: War Games No Threat to Gulf States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei said that the ongoing military maneuvers were neither
threat to the Persian Gulf states nor to any other
neighboring countries, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
"Viewing the grand Tariq al-Qods (Path to Jerusalem)
maneuvers as a threat to regional countries is a pure
American-Zionist propaganda," he was quoted by the official news
agency IRNA in a report filed here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Ali Khamenei, also Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces,
said Wednesday that the presence of Iranian armed forces in
the Persian Gulf was based on the objective of safeguarding
the borders of Iran, ensuring the country's independence and
firmly standing against any oppressive and dominating power.
</P>
<P>
"The grand Tariq al-Qods maneuvers are a demonstration of
the power of a dignified and honorable nation desiring to make
use of its strength to lead a respectable life and decisively
confront enemies and transgressors," he stated.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Khamenei made the statement while
addressing tens of thousands of forces of the Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) which have converged on the
southern port city of Bandar Abbas to take part in the
maneuvers.
</P>
<P>
Some 200,000 marines and ground forces of the IRGC and Basij
(volunteers) forces are participating in the war games which
started from Tuesday afternoon and are scheduled to end today. The
games covered 2,000 kilometers of the western and southern borders
of Iran.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 vessels, some helicopters and military fighters
are involved in the maneuvers. Surface-to-air, surface-to-sea and
surface-to-surface missiles will be tested in the games.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also lashed out at the United States for "trying
to impose their domination through every possible means in order
to spread their octopus-like tentacles extend in every nook and
corner of the world."
</P>
<P>
He stated that the arrogant powers want to impose their
presence in all sensitive and strategic regions, vital waterways
and in areas where there are abundant natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei called on the armed forces to be prepared to encounter
any transgressor and domineering power. "Iran is determined to
safeguard its independence based on divine laws and teachings and
that it will never kneel down to the enemies," he said.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Iran and the United States have been
strained for 18 years since the two countries severed
diplomatic ties on April 7, 1980, in the wave of American
hostage crisis.
</P>
<P>
The United States has pursued the dual-containment policy
against Iran and Iraq and imposed sanction and embargo on
Iran on the charges of seeking weapons of mass destruction,
sponsoring terrorism and opposing the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about Iran's relations with Western countries, Khamenei
stated that the western countries will become equal business
partners for Iran only when they separate themselves from the
United States.
</P>
<P>
He warned western countries that if they consider themselves
as indivisible partners of the United States then they should
know that Iran will have nothing to do with them either
politically or economically.
</P>
<P>
"It would be a great mistake to assume that the Islamic
Republic of Iran would be forced to maintain its relations
with a specific group," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
