<HEADLINE> East China Coastal City Expanding Wholesale Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Weihai, a coastal city in east
China's Shandong Province, is accelerating the building of five
major wholesale markets in an effort to develop local resources.
</P>
<P>
The city will expand the scale of local trading sites for
aquatic products, in a bid to build the country's largest aquatic
products wholesale market.
</P>
<P>
Weihai is an important fishery base in China, with the output
of aquatic products accounting for 12 percent of the country's
total.
</P>
<P>
As Weihai is a major fruit production base, the city plans to
build a fruit wholesale market in its downtown area.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last month, the Ministry of Internal Trade
approved the first national-level wholesale market for automobiles
for the farming purpose in Weihai. Preparatory work for the market
has started. The first-phase project, with a coverage of 42,000 sq
m, will be completed by June of this year.
</P>
<P>
The city will also build and upgrade a number of wholesale
markets for vegetable, capital goods, and farm and sideline
products, sources say. 
</P>
