<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Securities Watchdog To Launch Risk-Prevention Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The China Securities
Regulatory Commission, the industry watchdog, will keep a tighter
rein on the securities market to effectively ward off market
hazards.
</P>
<P>
And the commission has decided to start a nationwide
risk-prevention campaign to increase the risk awareness of
investors, forge a comprehensive risk management and prevention
system and improve the ability to waylay unsound investment
decisions.
</P>
<P>
"Risk prevention has a great bearing on the stable and
sustained development of China's securities market, and is
conducive to a healthy national economy and stable society," said
the spokesman of the CSRC, while pointing out that China's
securities market is still immature and the task of risk
prevention remains difficult.
</P>
<P>
Various educational activities will be held to hammer an
awareness of risks into the minds of investors, and the commission
is also seeking to improve its market information system for a
closer supervision on the market.
</P>
<P>
The surveillance system in the stock exchanges will also be
perfected to step up the frontline supervision of the securities
market.
</P>
<P>
To build a complete risk prevention system and effectively
steer clear of risks, the commission has called on securities
regulators at all levels to focus on market supervision and risk
prevention, while tightening the grip on stock exchanges, futures
exchanges, securities companies, securities registering and
settlement companies, listed companies, brokerage agencies of all
kinds and the media.
</P>
<P>
Special funds will also be set up for the risk prevention work.
</P>
<P>
The commission also encouraged the whole society to take part
in the risk prevention campaign by actively reporting market
irregularities either to securities regulators or stock
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The CSRC will set up a special office to act as the organizer
and coordinator of the campaign, and hold inspection tours
nationwide to promote the risk prevention drive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
