<HEADLINE> China Makes Headway In Capital Construction(1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China has made outstanding
achievements in investment-consuming capital construction, which
manifects national strength and speed of economic growth.
</P>
<P>
According to recent statistics, total investment in fixed
assets was almost 2.37 trillion yuan last year, an increase of 18.2
percent from the previous year, and 134 projects were completed.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the country's power capacity increased by 15.25
million kw, crude oil by 19.73 million tons. Total length of its
expressway network extended by 1,117 km, and that of railways,
1,954 km, in addition to 20,000 km wavelength of optical fibre and
21.07 million sets of telephone switchboards .
</P>
<P>
Most of the investment in these projects came from both central
and local government, with some coming from overseas investors, a
Chinese official says, but the government is still the biggest
investor.
</P>
<P>
Economists say that cash inflows from abroad are still a key
factor in China's economic take-off, as the country should be
backed by massive capital construction in infrastructure and basic
industries, which have always been a bottleneck in the
economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
