<HEADLINE> Police Launch Patrols in Dar es Salaam, Its </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Police units will be
deployed in greater numbers to curb escalating crime in Dar es
Salaam, the capital of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Regional Police Commander (RPC) Alfred Gewe said in an
interview on Tuesday that patrol squads would cover the city
center and suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Numerous units would be deployed in the suburbs in a wave of
robberies.
</P>
<P>
Specific points would be placed under guard as they are
reckoned to be hideouts of hard-core criminals, according to the
RPC.
</P>
<P>
Existing police posts are not sufficiently manned for mounting
extensive patrol duties in the various suburbs, he said.
</P>
<P>
Reinforcements would therefore be needed from the
centrally-placed police stations in each district, Gewe added.
</P>
<P>
An elaborate security strategy would be put into action to
ensure that crime at night was put at bay. People must be assured
of a peaceful life, the RPC emphasized.
</P>
<P>
"Police alone cannot succeed to deter criminals from pursuing
their wrongful missions. They need the help of Good Samaritans",
he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Available data indicate that there are fewer incidents of
crimes in the city in comparison with the last three years, he
revealed.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, "We want to ensure that the city is as
peaceful as possibe". 
</P>
