<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Pair Cooperation in Poverty Relief Runs High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's economically developed
provinces and municipalities have joined the country in its effort
to help poorer western parts come up to their level of development.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from better-off areas have been heading west,
responding to the central government's call last year to aid their
poor western counterparts with poverty relief projects.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Department of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
recently received six million yuan from eastern coastal Fujian
Province for aid-the-poor projects. Fujian's Putian County signed
a potato starch processing agreement this January with Ningxia's
Xiji County that involves 300 million yuan in investment. The
factory will be built to produce 60,000 tons of starch and 40,000
tons of feed annually, worth 500 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, northeast China's Liaoning Province is taking
responsibility for 676,000 needy people in 14 counties in Qinghai
Province in the northwest. Liaoning will donate materials and
technical assistance worth 43 million yuan, and will provide 1.54
million tons of grain and two million pieces of garments and
quilts over the next two years for needy Tibetan herdsmen who were
affected by a snowstorm last year.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has also sent engineers, agronomists, teachers, and
technicians to help Qinghai improve its industrial and
agricultural production, as well as education, and management.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between Shanghai, China's largest industrial city,
and southwestern Yunnan Province with its abundance of ethnic
groups is a combination of capital and resources. The city is
taking its capital, advanced managerial techniques, and skilled
personnel to Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
"Quicker economic growth in central and western China will in
turn promote the coordinated growth of the nation's economy as a
whole," said Xu Kuangdi, mayor of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Bustling Guangdong Province, south China, is making every
effort to help its neighbor to the west, the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region. It has set aside 60 million yuan to help
resettle 200,000 poor people in Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
This paired cooperation has shown itself to be something more
than charity -- it is, in fact, a partnership that benefits both.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
