<HEADLINE> Chinese Divers Lead Three Events in FINA Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese divers lead three out of
four events in the third FINA Diving Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
According to latest edition of The World of Swimming, FINA's
magizine, Chinese divers lead men's platform, 3-meter springboard
and women's platform after the first five legs of the 12-leg grand
prix series.
</P>
<P>
Chinese divers only took part in the competitions in China, New
Zealand and Australia and skipped the competitions in Russia and
Germany. Yet they still showed their supermacy in most events of
the sport.
</P>
<P>
Yu Zhuocheng leads men's springboard ranking with 150 points.
He is followed by his compatriot Zhou Yilin in the second place at
120. Stefan Ahrens of Germany is third with 90 points.
</P>
<P>
Sun Shuwei, world and Olympic champion who came back to the
sport after an eye surgery, received a perfect point of 180 in
three outings. Russ Bertram of the United States is second at 137
with Viadimir Timoshinin of Russia in the third place at 120.
</P>
<P>
Wang Rui also dominated the competitions she took part in and
registered a total of 180 points. Olga Khristoforova of Russia
collected 115 points for the second place. Elena Zhupina, an
Olympian from Ukraine, came third at 105 points.
</P>
<P>
The women's springboard saw Irina Vygouzova of Kazakhstan surge
ahead with 123 points. Yulia Pakalina of Russia and Zhupina are
second and third respectively.
</P>
<P>
Double Olympic gold medalist Fu Mingxia of China didn't take
part in any of the competitions. There are speculations that the
diving sensation at the Atlanta Olympic Games will probably retire
from international competitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
