<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Customers Buys Home-made Brands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's customers are buying more
Chinese-made commodities, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing based newspaper also reports that at least 90
percent of the refrigerators, washing machines and ventilators
sold in China last year were made by Chinese enterprises,
according to a survey conducted by the State Statistics Bureau,
ministries of Labour, Civil Affairs and Public Health, the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions and the People's Bank of
China.
</P>
<P>
The sample survey covered 200 million Chinese consumers in 71
major cities of the country's 30 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions. It included the sales of 40 kinds of products,
involving 12,000 brands make by Chinese and foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Of the 40 kinds of products covered in the survey, Chinese
companies have become the major suppliers of 33, dominating more
than 70 percent fo the market share in China. The survey shows
that 80 percent of the products sold in China last year were made
by Chinese companies.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the survey as saying that the majority of the
Chinese families expressed their willingness to buy Chinese-made
electrical appliances rather than foreign ones when it is time to
replace their present models.
</P>
<P>
Domestically made products often fetch lower prices than those
made abroad, so Chinese families buying domestic appliances can
save money and, at the same time, get a quality product. To
complete with their Chinese counterparts, some foreign companies
have also had to re-adjust their marketing strategies to
strengthen their presence in the marketplace. The paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
