<HEADLINE> Five-Nation Accord on Border Arms Reduction to Be Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China, Russia, Kazakhstan,
Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan will sign an agreement here this morning
on the mutual reduction of military forces in the border areas
between China and the four countries -- the first treaty of its
kind in the Asia-Pacific region. .
</P>
<P>
The agreement, a result of over seven years of negotiations, is
expected to set detailed limits to the numbers of military
personnel and weapons deployed in the designated areas along the
border between China and the four former Soviet republics.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of the five nations signed an agreement on
military confidence-building in the border areas, in China's
largest city of Shanghai on April 26 last year. 
</P>
