<HEADLINE> Spain Celebrates Birthday of Don Quixote Author </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID April 23 (Xinhua) -- Spanish seminars, exhibitions, book
fairs, theaters and movies have been involved in various
activities in recent days to commemorate the 450th anniversary of
the birth of Miguel Saavedra de Cervantes, the author of Don
Quixote.
</P>
<P>
One activity has been the relay recital of Don Quixote. For two
days and nights without respite, fans from all walks of life went
on stage one-by-one to read out aloud the best-known Spanish novel.
</P>
<P>
At the commemoration center in the capital, literature buffs
lined up, awaiting their turn to contribute a chapter for a long
novel in an activity called "One Thousand People Writing one Book."
</P>
<P>
Born on April 23, 1574, Cervantes was one of the most prominent
literary figures in Spain during the Renaissance. His novel, Don
Quixote, the story about a hapless knight who tried to save the
world, is one of the most successful and popular works in
literature history.
</P>
<P>
This year, Spain is planning to publish an encyclopedia on
Cervantes, and put all of his works on the internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
