<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Andean Community to Boost Ties with Countries, Blocs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUCRE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Community is to speed up
its integration with regional economic blocs and countries across
the world in line with the trend towards globalization.
</P>
<P>
A pact signed today by presidents of the four Andean Community
members -- Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador and Venezuela, said the
group will speed up negotiations with the South American Common
Market (Mercosur) and the 15-nation European Union (EU) for closer
ties.
</P>
<P>
It also pledged to conclude negotiations for a free trade
agreement with South America's biggest trade bloc Mercosur,
embracing Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, by this year.
</P>
<P>
Bolivian President Gonzalo Sanchez de Lozada and his Paraguayan
counterpart Juan Carlos Wasmosy, the current Mercosur president,
today signed a joint statement, reaffirming their commitment to
form a free trade zone as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The group will institutionalize dialogue with China, following
the group's successful practice of regular contact with India. It
will also promote cooperation with the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
The group, which regretted Peru's decision to quit earlier
this month, pledged to begin talks with Panama this year on a free
trade agreement which would form the basis for Panama's formal
entry into the bloc. They will try to clinch the deal by June 30,
1998.
</P>
<P>
The group also vowed to actively join in international forums,
particularly in the negotiations for a Free Trade Area of the
Americas (FTAA), which would create a free trade zone from Canada
to Chile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
