<HEADLINE> Shougang Seeks Technological Back-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Shougang Group reached an
agreement yesterday in Beijing with a research association to seek
additional technological back-up for its development over the next
year, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The China Research Association for Economy and Technology will
focus this year through next year on a feasibility study of
Shougang's development strategy for 2000-2010, said association
director Wu Mingyu at a signing ceremony yesterday.
</P>
<P>
It will also help the group hold technological seminars and
symposiums on metallurgical, information and real-estate industry
development.
</P>
<P>
The Shougang Group, a large state firm specializing mainly in
iron and steel production, has 28 subsidiaries in 14 provinces and
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two sides will hold regular
exchanges. Shougang is expected to report its operations and
production to the association while the latter will make more
efforts in developing products and opening markets.
</P>
<P>
Wu said his association, a subsidiary of the Chinese
Association for Science and Technology (Cast), has set up expert
groups providing support in the fields of steel and iron,
machinery, electronics, architecture, shipping and finance --
which constitute the group's businesses.
</P>
<P>
Such co-operation marks the beginning of the linking of
campaigns between state-owned enterprises and research
institutions. These links were launched early this year by Cast,
the country's largest non-governmental organization featuring the
dissemination of scientific and technological knowledge.
</P>
<P>
Cast has called on its branches across the country and local
technological associations to help 1,000 research institutions
join with 1,000 state-owned enterprises propel technology
renovation, energy-saving and cost-cutting technology,
product-quality improvements and new-product development.
</P>
<P>
The move is a key program of Cast this year, said senior
association official Zhang Yutai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
