corridor was more economic than others linking Central Asia with
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Akayev said that he has supported the idea of commonwealth, but
any haste can wreck integration process of the CIS.
</P>
<P>
As for the Russian-Belarussian Union, the two presidents
indicated that it is an internal matter for Moscow and Minsk to
decide.
</P>
<P>
Akayev is expected to arrive in Moscow later today to sign a
five-nation agreement on the reduction of military forces in the
areas along the borders of Russia, Kazakhstan, Kirghizia,
Tajikistan and China. The agreement will be signed Thursday.
