<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Reduce Natural Gas Consumption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine plans to reduce its natural
gas consumption by five to seven billion cubic meters this year.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the use of gas meters will be introduced into
every household, Minister of State Affairs Anatoly Minchenko said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The government will then change its way of collecting gas
fees. The present system is based on the size of the family, not
on the actual amount consumed by the family, causing tremendous
waste in this energy-starved country, Minchenko said.
</P>
<P>
He said since Ukraine does not produce gas meters, it will set
up a joint venture with a British partner.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine consumes 90 billion cubic meters of natural gas every
year, with 53 billion imported from Russia and 20 billion from
Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
To lessen the energy crisis, industries of metallurgy,
chemistry, coal mining and machine-building will be among the
first required to use energy-saving technologies, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
