<HEADLINE> Cuba Looks to Hydrogen Fuel Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Cuban authorities have formed a
special group to stimulate research on the use of hydrogen as
fuel that could be used in place of petroleum in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Hydrogen is the most abundant element on the planet and its
combustion does not contaminate the atmosphere since it only
produces steam, Dr. Vito Quevedo, the chief of the National
Program for the Development of Sustainable Energy Sources, said
today.
</P>
<P>
The group for studying hydrogen as a renewable energy source
will collate all the work being done in the country to speed up
research, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the first stage of research, the group will seek all the
information available worldwide on the practical uses of hydrogen.
</P>
<P>
The experts will continue to investigate the use of solar
energy to produce cheap electricity in order to obtain hydrogen
through the decomposition of water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
