<HEADLINE> Andean Summit Approves Creation of Andean Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUCRE, BOLIVIA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A summit meeting of the
four-nation South American free-trade bloc, the Andean Community,
today approved a treaty to create an Andean Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Each member country will send five parliamentary
representatives to sit in the parliament which will discuss the
integration process between the four nations.
</P>
<P>
The parliament will be based in the Colombian capital Santafe
de Bogota.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community, which changed its name from the Andean
Group during the summit , groups Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador and
Venezuela. Peru announced it was leaving the group earlier
this month after other members refused to grant it exemptions from
tariff reductions. 
</P>
