<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China and Russia signed a joint statement yesterday on
promoting the multipolarization of the world and the establishment
of a new world order.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a just and equitable new international
political and economic order based on peace and stability has
become the pressing need of the times and the inevitable necessity
of history, it said.
</P>
<P>
The statement called for elimination of hegemonism and power
politics in the world. Both sides stand for the establishment of a
new and universally applicable security concept, believing that
the "Cold War mentality" must be abandoned and bloc politics
opposed, it said.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and his Russian counterpart
Boris Yeltsin pledged yesterday to further strengthen the two
countries' strategic coordination partnership of equality and
mutual confidence oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"China's policy of developing partnership with Russia is not a
makeshift and will not be hampered by any temporary incidence,"
said Jiang during their talks in the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents hailed their joint statement on the
multipolarization of the world and the establishment of a new
international order, saying it indicated their common views on the
basic trend of the post-Cold War international situation and their
identical stands on major international issues.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua News Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- WTO director-general Renato Ruggiero said yesterday that he
was optimistic about China's accession to the World Trade
Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero said that the WTO is satisfied with the efforts and
response that China has made in its bid to join the WTO. He said
that as long as all parties show a sense of urgency and necessary
flexibility and concentrate on the process of negotiation, they
will finally achieve a balance of interest.
</P>
<P>
He hopes that the next round of negotiation on China's
accession to the WTO in May will achieve more progress on the
issue and maintain the momentum of previous negotiations so as to
conclude the issue on an earliest possible date.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China plans to launch a series of theme tour drives in the
next three years to attract more overseas visitors to the country.
</P>
<P>
The theme for 1998 will be "China Urban and Rural Tours" to
show its 5,000-year-old culture and the changes due to the
opening-up policy since 1979.
</P>
<P>
China will introduce the "Ecotourist Tour" in 1999 to meet the
trend of international ecotourist development, and to celebrate
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China and the resumption of exercise of sovereignty over Macao.
</P>
