<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 138 Year Old Woman Discovered in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Maria del Pilar, a 138 year-old
Ecuadoran woman, who is blind and invalid, could be recognized in
the Guinness Book of Records as the oldest woman in the world.
</P>
<P>
The old lady's existence came to light after a granddaughter
requested help from the local press for a reunion between the old
woman and her 110 year-old blind daughter, who had not been able
to meet her mother in the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Maria del Pilar was born in 1859 in Guayaquil, Ecuador's
biggest industrial city, and at the age of 15 married Escencio
Gurumendi with whom she bore five daughters and eight sons of
which only six remain. Two of them lived past 90.
</P>
<P>
An invalid since she fell in her home on the outskirts of
Guayaquil four years ago, the oldest woman in Ecuador shows signs
of the passing of the years. She is very thin, cannot hear or see
and can only murmur.
</P>
<P>
When one of her daughters was asked the secret of Maria del
Pilar's longevity, she answered that "she eats a chicken every day
 and that is why she raises her own chickens."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
