<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone Yields Good Economic Result </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Development Zone in
the north Chinese port city of the same name has become the
largest and most profitable zone of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
Work on the zone began 12 years ago, and by last year it had a
GDP of 13.1 billion yuan and 43.3 billion yuan in industrial
output value. Its exports last year totalled 1.45 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
It has attracted 8.2 billion US dollars worth of overseas
investment from 62 countries and regions, and has more than 2,800
foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In order to improve its investment environment, the zone will
give priority to developing its service industry by setting up
four centers in the 1996-2000 period for direct marketing of
industrial goods, production materials, farm and sideline
products, and products of its foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
By the turn of the century, annual investment in the service
trade in the zone is expected to be one billion yuan, which is
expected to help add more than two billion yuan in output value a
year.
</P>
<P>
The zone has developed a series of preferential policies for
taxes, rents, loans, and information to encourage overseas
business people to increase investment locally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
