<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves $328 Mln for Four Projects in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of a total of 328 million U.S. dollars loans for four
projects in three Latin American nations.
</P>
<P>
A 125 million dollar loan is earmarked for Argentina Provincial
Agricultural Development Project. The project will help introduce
new farming technologies, modern varieties of crops, and increase
services from the private sector. The project will benefit 120,000
small-and medium-sized commercial farms to increase and diversify
their crops and exports as well as improve land productivity.
</P>
<P>
A total of 190 million dollars are provided for Brazil. A 90
million dollar loan will help the country's land reform and
poverty alleviation and another 100 million dollar loan will
finance Brazil resource management and help build needed
agricultural infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The Bank also okayed a 13 million dollar loan for Guatemala.
The project will provide technical assistance to the Guatemalan
government for designing regulations, strengthening regulatory
agencies, and managing its privatization program for
transportation, power, postal and telecommunications services.
</P>
</TEXT>
