<HEADLINE> Technology Group: Germany Should Be European No.1 in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A top German research and technology
advisory group today called on the Bonn government, business and
researchers to make coordinated efforts with an aim to make
Germany the Number One in Europe in applying biotechnologies.
</P>
<P>
In a special report issued today, the Committee for Research,
Technology and Innovation, which was set up by German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl, made altogether 96 recommendations with a view to
promote further development of biotechnology in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Among other things, the committee called for improved
cooperation between business and science in order to make full
commercial use of biotechnologies.
</P>
<P>
The committee also urged the government to provide tax
preference in order to mobilize more risk capitals in
biotechnologies and to encourage the establishment of new
enterprises and the expansion of existing firms applying
biotechnologies.
</P>
<P>
The committee also called for improved public education and
patent protection for biotech development.
</P>
<P>
Chaired by German research minister Juergen Ruettgers, the
committee consists of five government ministers and a number of
leading figures from business circles, trade unions, research
units and universities.  
</P>
