<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Edge Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Leading technology stocks in New
York surged today in advance of IBM's earnings report, but the
broad market edged lower as interest rates rose.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average lost 20.87 points to 6,812.72.
The blue chip gauge surged 173 points, or 2.6 percent, its second
biggest point gain ever and its largest percentage gain since late
1991.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 6-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 489.24 million
shares as against 488.61 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 0.97 to 773.64, the
NYSE composite index fell 1.13 to 404.71, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index fell 1.60 to 543.36.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq market posted a big gain, rising
14,41 points to 1,227.15, but most market indicators edged lower.
</P>
<P>
The bond market gave back Tuesday's gains, pushing interest
rates back up and giving pressure on stock market.
</P>
<P>
Major technology shares such as Intel and Microsoft, however,
rallied amid hopes that IBM would also report strong first-quarter
results. After the close of trading, IBM reported a 1.2 billion
U.S. dollar profit that was slightly above analyst expectations.
</P>
<P>
In other earnings news, DuPont and Walt Disney both reported
better than expected earnings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
