<HEADLINE> China Ambassador on Arms Control, Disarmament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Sha Zukang, Chinese
Ambassador for Disarmament Affairs, said on Wednesday that the
international community is facing both opportunities and
challenges in the field of international arms control and
disarmament under the current world situation.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that as an important multilateral deliberative organ
on disarmament, the U.N. Disarmament Commission (UNDC) will be
able to make new contributions to disarmament by adapting to the
changed international situation.
</P>
<P>
On the opportunities and challenges, Ambassador Sha noted that
at present, the overall international situation continues to move
toward relaxation.
</P>
<P>
"However,"he said. "there are still many destabilizing and
uncertain elements affecting the international situation.
</P>
<P>
"It is especially noteworthy that after the end of the military
confrontation between the Eastern and Western blocs, some
countries still adhere to the Cold War thinking," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, some regions remain suffering from turbulence and
conflicts, and the situation in some hot spots is deteriorating,"
he said. "Under such circumstances, we are facing both
opportunities and challenges in the field of international arms
control and disarmament."
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Sha made the remarks at the plenary meeting of the
1997 UNDC, whose main topics this year are Special Session on
Disarmament IV, nuclear-weapon-free zones and guidelines on
conventional arms control and disarmament.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Sha said under the new circumstances following the
Cold War, it is obviously necessary to convene the Fourth Special
Session on Disarmament.
</P>
<P>
Noting the ever increasing nuclear-weapon-free zones, he
stressed the importance of formulating guiding principles for the
establishment of nuclear-weapon-free zone, especially those
concerning the geographical demarcation of the zones and their
relationship with existing international law.
</P>
<P>
On conventional arms control, Ambassador Sha that the
deliberation on this item should be confined to the consolidation
of peace through conventional arms control and disarmament in
regions that have suffered from conflicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
