<HEADLINE> Mobutu's Special Envoy Arrives in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Zairean President Mobutu's
special adviser, Honore Ngbanda, arrived here tonight to convey
Mobutu's reply to South African President Nelson Mandela's formal
invitation last week to meet Zairean rebel leader Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
But it is still not known what reply is going to be delivered
to the South African government by Mobutu over the negotiation
invitation.
</P>
<P>
Ngbanda and his entourage were driven away from Johannesburg
International Airport to Pretoria in a convoy of high-powered
motor vehicles shortly after their arrival.
</P>
<P>
Ngbanda is not expected to meet South African Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki, a leading peace broker in Zairean crisis, said
government officials.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki's spokesman Thami Nteniteni said in Pretoria that he was
not aware of a meeting between the deputy president and the envoy
tonight.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports quoted Foreign Affairs Ministry spokesman
Pieter Swanepoel as saying that Ngbanda had reportedly asked to
meet Mbeki. 
</P>
