<HEADLINE> Camerounian PM Urges Investment in African Franc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Camerounian Prime Minister Peter
Mafany Musonge today called on the international community to
promote investment in Africa's Franc Zone.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the opening ceremony of the second
regional meeting of the International Labor Organization (ILO) on
the social economic consequencies of the devaluation of the CFA
currency.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister urged the participants of the meeting to
work out proper solutions to minimize the difficulties resulting
from the devaluation of the CFA currency in 1994 which was
accompanied by immediate social economic and inflationary
hardship.
</P>
<P>
He said Cameroun has elaborated a new policy on employment and
professional training and put in place a program to encourage
small and medium size enterprises.
</P>
<P>
On his part, ILO regional director Elias Mabere emphasised the
need to protect the workers and fight poverty.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and experts from 14 African Franc Zone
countries attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
