<HEADLINE> Dortmund Reaches Champions' Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Borussia Dortmund
edged Manchester United 1-0 in the second leg here Wednesday
night, reaching the European Champions' Cup soccer final with an
aggregate score of 2-0.
</P>
<P>
The German club, which won the first leg two weeks ago, has
been on defensive most of the time and scored the lone goal in a
counter-attack through striker Lars Ricken at the eighth minute.
</P>
<P>
Ricken connected a pass on the right side and made a lightning
turn-around to left-foot the ball into the far corner of the net.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, which has won four Premier Leagues in the
latest five seasons and now is a runaway leader with only four
rounds to go in the league, has squandered many chances to
overcome the deficit.
</P>
<P>
French star Erik Cantona wasted an excellent chance when he,
with only one man to beat, hesitated in front of the goal. Andy
Cole, one of England's most expensive stars, also missed several
chances to level the score.
</P>
<P>
The English club has sixty percent of possession and got 14
corner shots against the rival's four.
</P>
<P>
Security had been tightened around the Old Trafford Football
Ground before two teams' supporters poured into narrow entrances
to 43,000-seat stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
