<HEADLINE> Juventus Beats Ajax 4-1 to Enter Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Italiay league leader Juventus
trounced Ajax 4-1 to enter the final of the European Champions
Cup.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, defending champion of the tournament, won the first
leg of the semi-final 2-1 and advanced into the final with a 6-2
aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Attilio Lombardo was the hero of the match. He scored one
goal and set up another in the match.
</P>
<P>
Ajax dominated the early play of the match played in Turin on
Wednesday, but failed to hold on their stamina.
</P>
<P>
Lombardo got away from his marker on a corner kick and headed
home in the 34th minute.
</P>
<P>
Lombardo then streaked up the left flank and sent a accurate
cross to Christian Vieri. Vieri launched home a left-foot for
his fourth Champions Cup goal.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team will meet German club Borussia Dortmund in
the final at Munich, Germany, on May 28. 
