<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Vow to Strengthen Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
his Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin pledged today to further
strengthen the two countries' strategic coordination partnership
of equality and mutual confidence oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During their talks in the Kremlin, the fourth official meeting
between the two leaders, Jiang said, "China's policy of
developing partnership with Russia is not a makeshift and will not
be hampered by any temporary incidence."
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to make continuous efforts together with
Russia to deepen and strengthen cooperation on both bilateral ties
and international issues," he added.
</P>
<P>
Before their talks, Yeltsin presided over a ceremony in the
Kremlin to greet Jiang, who arrived here Tuesday for a five-day
state visit.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin described Jiang's visit as of historic significance and
said the two leaders will jointly make decisions on the future of
the bilateral relations for early next century.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents hailed their joint statement on the
multipolarization of the world and the establishment of a new
international order, saying it indicated their common views on the
basic trend of the post-Cold War international situation and their
identical stands on major international issues.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that the Sino-Russian partnership, a new type
of state-to-state relations based on the Five Principles of
Peaceful Coexistence, is not any kind of alliance directed at any
other countries.
</P>
<P>
Both countries are willing to develop friendly cooperation with
other countries in the world on the basis of mutual respect,
equality and mutual benefit, they said at their talks.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that to date, Russia has not signed any document
similar to the joint statement with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Yeltsin's major contribution to the
establishment of the two countries' strategic coordination
partnership.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment and development of the
Sino-Russian strategic coordination partnership fully conform with
the fundamental interests of the two countries and two peoples,
and are in line with the trend and requirements of the world
situation and international relations in the post-Cold War era.
</P>
<P>
Such a partnership, featuring equality and mutual confidence,
good-neighborliness and friendship, and mutually beneficial
cooperation, will undoubtedly facilitate the mutual development
and prosperity of the two neighbors and benefit the two peoples,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the partnership is also of far-reaching
historic significance in safeguarding independence, sovereignty,
national dignity and legitimate interests of both countries as
well as ensuring balance of world powers and setting up a new
international political and economic order of peace, stability,
fairness and rationalization, Jiang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
