his visit to Jordan aimed at discussing bilateral relations,
particularly in the economic fields.
</P>
<P>
He said in order to promote the ties, an agreement was reached
with the Jordanian side to activate the joint Jordanian-Malaysian
supreme committee, adding that the prime ministers of the two
countries would be entrusted with the formation of this
committee. They will also establish a mechanism under the
co-chairmanship of the foreign ministers of the two countries,
which is to meet once a year in Amman and Kuala Lampur alternately.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the prospects of establishing
joint ventures in Jordan that would not only serve the Jordanian
market but the markets of neighboring countries as well. 
