"These aspired objectives can be attained within framework of
legal facilities stipulated in bilateral agreements, most notably
those related to encouragement and protection of investments and
averting dual taxation," Prodi was quoted by KUNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
Italy, one of the major western developed industrial
countries, has been maintaining a strong political ties with
Kuwait since 1968. It took part in the U.S.-led alliance which
liberated Kuwait from the seven-month Iraqi occupation in the
Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Since the Gulf War, Italian and Kuwaiti officials exchanged
several visits. Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh
Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah visited Rome last December.
</P>
<P>
On the economic front, Kuwait and Italy signed an agreement
on the development of economic, industrial, technical and
financial cooperation in 1986 and another accord on the
protection of investment in 1987. The latter took effect in
May 1990.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to avoid double taxation also took effect in
1993.
</P>
<P>
Italy ranks seventh among the exporting countries to Kuwait
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Prodi was accompanied by a high-level delegation and this is
his first Gulf tour since he took office in last May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970424.0326 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cases of Car Theft Drop in Lagos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Cases of car theft in Nigeria's
commercial center of Lagos has dropped remarkably in the past few
months, according to the official News Agency of Nigeria today.
</P>
<P>
It quoted police statistics as saying that while 1,633 cars
were stolen in the first six months of 1996, the figure dropped
to 1,202 during the period from August 1996 to February this
year.
</P>
<P>
On average, six cars are stolen everyday this year, compared
to nine last year, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The police recovered a total of 1,906 stolen cars throughout
1996, while 154 vehicles were recovered in the first two months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
A senior police source has attributed the decrease of car theft
cases to the state government's Operation Sweep aimed at cracking
down armed robbery and other serious crimes.
</P>
<P>
The police has wiped out many robbery gangs and increased its
patrols along the border with the Benin Republic, which had been the
outlet for stolen cars from Nigeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
