<HEADLINE> Eritrea's Ruling Party Holds 6th Central </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The 6th central committee
meeting of the ruling Eritrean People's Front for Democracy and
Justice opened on Tuesday in capital Asmara, according to a
report from the Voice of Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The radio reported that the meeting discussed last year's
performance in the political, economic and social sectors after
hearing reports.
</P>
<P>
It said the meeting has reaffirmed the party's commitment to
the prevalence of peace and the respect for justice and equality
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The party would continue working at the prevalence of peace
and stability in neighboring countries and friendly relations
with countries in the east African sub-region.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1969, it became a ruling party of the country
since the liberation of Eritrea in 1991. Its previous name was
Eritrean People's Liberation Front before 1994. 
</P>
