<HEADLINE> Cameroun to Extend Coop with France in Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Camerounian health authority
today called on French-speaking African countries to extend
closer cooperation with French pharmaceutical industries to
acquire advanced technology for local production.
</P>
<P>
Alim Hayatou, secretary of state for public health of
Cameroun, made the call while opening a three-day seminar on drug
manufacturing in French-speaking Africa and France.
</P>
<P>
Drug manufacturers and distributors drawn from seven
French-speaking African countries and France probed ways of
fighting illegal drug selling, increase people's access to
locally-made drugs and enhancing the role of health authority in
reducing drug prices.
</P>
<P>
The Yaounde seminar is a follow-up to the meeting which took
place in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, in 1994, attended by African
drug authorities and pharmaceutical industries. 
