<HEADLINE> Angola Willing to Contribute to Solution of Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A joint special envoy of the
United Nations and the Organization of African Unity said here
today that Angola, as Zaire's neighbor, can contribute to a
political settlement of the Zaire crisis.
</P>
<P>
UN/OAU envoy Mohammed Sahnoun made the remarks after his
meeting with Angolan President Eduardo Dos Santos.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, President Dos Santos said that he is
willing to try his best for a peaceful solution to the escalating
Zaire crisis, according to Sahnoun.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan president added that if necessary, he will
meditate between the conflicting sides to persuade them to solve
their problems by negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun told reporter that progress has been made in seeking a
political solution to the Zaire crisis.
</P>
<P>
After the two sides agreed to hold negotiations on a
transition period before the general elections scheduled for
April 8, they also greed to hold a summit meeting between
President Mobutu Sese Seko and rebel leader Laurent Kabila, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
However, the summit meeting was postponed because of Mobutu's
ill health, Sahnoun said, adding that the two sides will choose a
new venue for the possible summit meeting or decide resume
dialogue between their delegations.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun, who arrived here earlier today, will also meet UN
special envoy based in Angola, Blondin Beye, before returning to
South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
