<HEADLINE> Parties Apply for Legislative Elections in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Out of the 79 political parties
that expressed their wish to participate in the May 17
legislative elections in Cameroun, only 42 so far have actually
deposit their lists for the various constituencies.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed today by officials from the Ministry of
Territorial Administration.
</P>
<P>
Among the 42 parties, 19 are running in only one constituency.
Eight are going in for the competition in two constituencies. But
some big parties like the ruling Cameroun People's Democratic
Movement have presented in 42 constituencies, topping the list so
far.
</P>
<P>
Despite that fact that the deadline for the handing in of the
list of candidates in expired April 17, Ebang Otong, director of
political affairs in the ministry, reiterated the government's
decision to be flexible in the respect of deadlines during the
preparatory phase.
</P>
<P>
That means more applications could be received from the party
candidates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
